I hope to eventually have a KiCad exporter. This would require full pin number information. So I'm wondering if we can enhance the per-component YAML format To include this meta-data. It would not be used except by exporters. This would require updating all the existing YAML files. Thoughts?

This is the right instinct — the exporter-side lookup table I hand-waved for NDL would rot; the component YAML, which already cites its datasheet, is the natural home for this knowledge. It's very doable, and I'd shape it like this:

Keep it out of pins:. FR-062's ban on power/ground pins isn't an accident — every rule downstream of pins: assumes signal pins (required direction, side/position, group coherence, unique names feeding saved endpoints). Adding power pins there means carving exceptions through all of that. Instead, add a separate optional top-level block that the editor and simulator never read:

physical:
  package: DIP-14            # tool-neutral footprint hint
  power:
    - { name: VCC, number: 14, rail: 5v }
    - { name: GND, number: 7 }
  nc: [ 13 ]                 # no-connects, if any

This follows the FR-066 precedent (the behavior: block is opaque to everything except its one consumer), so the parser change is nearly nil and no editor behavior is touched.

The validation is where the value is. Once physical: exists, the server can cross-check what today is uncheckable: signal-pin numbers plus power/NC numbers must be unique and must exactly tile 1..N for the declared package. That completeness check will catch transcription errors in the existing number: fields that nothing currently exercises — the same class of bug the NDL example's unconnected-wiper errata illustrated. I'd make the check conditional on the block being present, so parts without it (fictional ones like type-RAM256-8, dialog-created GALs) stay legal and the exporter just warns.

A pleasant free ride: FR-057 copies the full type YAML into every saved instance, so physical: flows into save files automatically — no save-format change, no formatVersion bump, and exporters (NDL, KiCad) can work from the design JSON alone without consulting the library.

Scope of the update: 33 files. The 31 74-series parts are mostly mechanical — HC-family corner power (Vcc = top corner, GND = pin N/2 is the usual pattern but not universal, so each one should be confirmed against the datasheet already cited in the file header). type-R8X8 needs numbers assigned (real SIP/DIP resistor packs exist to model it on); type-RAM256-8 is fictional and can simply omit the block. The make-yaml-from-datasheet skill should also be updated so new parts arrive with the block filled in.

Two things I'd defer but leave room for: per-instance footprint choice (DIP vs SOIC — the FR-058 override mechanism is the natural carrier when KiCad export actually lands), and tool-specific footprint IDs (Package_DIP:DIP-14_W7.62mm
— I'd keep the YAML tool-neutral and let the KiCad exporter own that mapping, with an optional escape-hatch field only if the mapping proves lossy).

Process-wise this is a clean additive change: a new suffixed FR (FR-062e, say) stating the block is exporter-only metadata ignored by editor and simulation, a design.md §7.6 addition, a CHANGELOG line, then the parser tweak + validation + the 33-file sweep. The datasheet verification pass is the only genuinely careful part.

